name: SAMUELS ELEMENTARY SOAR
details: Samuels Elementary School is a diverse, high-growth, high-performing elementary school in Southeast Denver. In addition to strong academic offerings and character education, students participate in the arts, technology and physical education.

name: KIDS ROCK UNIVERSITY
details:
Kids Rock University is a licensed childcare program for children ages 5-17 years old.  During the summer months there is a week long, full-day program.  The week includes three in-house days, two field trips, along with a variety of fun activities such as crafts, games, movies, cooking, music, drama, science, sports, playing outdoors, etc.  The KRU Clubhouse is located across the street from CCV High School on North B Street.

Every Tuesday is swimming and a movie and Friday’s trips vary weekly.  Some of the summer trips will be Elitch’s, bowling, lazer tag, Santa’s Workshop, Pirate’s Cove, It’z Family Fun Center, Cheyenne Mountain Zoo, and Trampoline World.  The “in house” days are just as much fun.  There will be skating, crafts, hula hoop contest, water slide, face painting, and outdoor games for examples.

There are some steps to take to get your child into the program.  There are a couple of forms to be filled out, a current immunization record MUST be turned in with the application, and there is a one time registration fee of $10.00 and a t-shirt will be provided.  The cost is $14/day plus activity fee and $11/day plus activity fee for an additional child.  There is a half day rate of $8.00 if a child attends less than 5 hours  a  day.  There is also financial aid available.  Lunches are provided through partnership with Care & Share.

name: MISSION VIEJO PRESCHOOL
details: Cherry Creek Early Childhood Program is dedicated to providing quality early childhood education to preschool children and families of all cultures, abilities, and circumstances in the Cherry Creek School District.

name: WILD BEAR CENTER FOR NATURE DISCOVERY
details: Wild Bear Mountain Ecology Center is a nonprofit, tax exempt corporation offering year round hands on, educational programs to people of all ages to foster a lifelong appreciation of the environment and to promote an environmentally aware, responsible and ecologically sound community.

name: HARRISON SCHOOL DISTRICT #2 GORMAN ED CTR
COWLIKS CHILD CARE CENTER
details: “Our mission is to provide the highest quality child care by creating a safe, healthy, and caring environment that promotes the physical, social, and emotional development of your child”

name: KENT DENVER SCHOOL
details: Excellence in scholarship and character is the goal of a Kent Denver education.  We seek to build a caring, diverse community of responsible citizens.  To that end, the school provides a challenging college preparatory curriculum and sets high ethical standards.

name: COMMUNITY PARTNERSHIP FOR CHILD DEVELOPMENT
details:
Founded in 1987, CPCD was spun-off from Catholic Charities to simply manage the Head Start program in El Paso County. At that time, CPCD was funded to serve 300 children. We now reach nearly six times that number through Head Start, Early Head Start and the Colorado Preschool Program.

CPCD now serves 1,899 families with children, ages 0-5, who are living in limited-income households, have special needs or are experiencing other difficult circumstances that could challenge their readiness for kindergarten. Last year, CPCD's waiting list topped 1,000.

The agency operates 60 classrooms in six local school districts. In addition to education, CPCD provides health, behavioral health, transportation, nutrition, home visits and family services. CPCD currently employs approximately 350 staff members. Both of these numbers may increase as we continue our ongoing expansion.

name: CLUB 4 KIDS, INC.
details: Club 4 Kids is Denver's original hourly drop-in child care center which was created for two equally important reasons.  First, to provide a safe environment for children to have fun, meet new friends, and enjoy an unstructured play environment.  And secondly, to provide parents with free time for themselves that is flexible, spontaneous, and affordable.  Club 4 Kids has been serving children and families in your community for over 16 years, and was recently voted "Best of the Best" child care center in Highlands Ranch by the Highlands Ranch Herald readers, and also "Best of the Best" in a Centennial reader's poll.
business hours:
Monday - Thursday
 8:30am - 9:00 pm

 Friday
 8:30am - 11:00pm

 Saturday
 10:00am - 11:00 pm

 Sunday

name: EXPLORE & DISCOVER: A HIGHLAND PARK COOPERATI
details: Explore and Discover (E&D)  is a Reggio Emilia-based daycare for children ages six weeks to 3 years, located in the heart of Denver’s West Highlands neighborhood. At E&D, children explore the world around them through play, and our teachers and parents participate as partners every day. E&D operates as a cooperative and families participate monthly in activities that support the program as well as attend parent meetings, parent-education seminars and special events.

name: WILSON CPCD PRESCHOOL
details: The mission of Community Partnership for Child Development is to prepare children for success in school and in life by providing excellent comprehensive early childhood services, in partnership with diverse families and the community.

name: KIDZAPALOOZA
details:
KIDZapalooza strives to allow the opportunity, in a safe learning environment, for our children to experience hands-on, minds-on, and feelings-on learning experiences. We consciously recognize opportunities for ‘teachable” moments throughout each day. Our curriculum is academic, social, and addresses different learning styles. The information is to be used as a guideline with flexibility built into the day allowing teachers the ability to make choices within an age appropriate scaffold learning curriculum. Choices should be based on what works best for each individual child, and should be beneficial in the teaching approach.
We are working alongside Qualistar for our accreditation in working with babies. Qualistar is a highly reputable organization that is working to make sure every child has the opportunity to excel at the highest level of  care, developmentally and educationally.
KIDZapalooza invites all families to come and tour the facility.
No appointment needed, stop in and see what we are doing at anytime during the day.
We offer a referral program to families. For every family referred get a week free** Call for details

name: MANY BLESSINGS CHILD CARE
details:
We believe that a child has the right to develop a positive self image.  It is our hope that by treating each child with love and respect he/she will learn to treat others with love and respect.

We believe that children learn best through interaction with their environment.  By offering a wide variety of experiences for children, we hop to arouse their curiosity, challenge their physical and mental abilities, and encourage self-expression.

Limits have been set to ensure the physical safety and emotional security of each individual child in ways which preserve the child's self-image and help to develop inner discipline.
business hours:
Monday to Friday
6:00 AM to 6:00 PM

name: GRAND KIDS CHILD CARE
details:
They are your early childhood connection in Grand County.  They collaborate by connecting parents, teachers and services to improve the lives of young children in Grand County.
They offer a Child Care Tuition Scholarship Program.  More more information visit their website: Grand Beginnings.

name: KIDS CAMPUS/CROWLEY CO CHILD CARE CTR
details: Kids' Campus, located in Ordway, offers superb daycare and pre-school services for young families. The small class sizes and dedicated, caring staff provide a fun, safe, kid-friendly environment for young children to excel. The daycare center at Kids' Campus offers excellent daycare and after school services for busy families at very reasonable rates. The state approved pre-school program combines stimulating class activities with fun field trips for hands-on learning to prepare children both socially and academically for school. At Kids' Campus they believe that healthy bodies go along with growing minds and the children are provided with nutritious meals and snacks throughout the day. The convenient hours, affordable rates, safe environment and fun factor all add up to Kids' Kids' Campus Day Car CenterCampus being the best place for young children to grow and learn in Crowley County.

name: YAMPAH MOUNTAIN HIGH SCHOOL NURSERY
details: Yampah Nurseries have been set up to provide a loving, nurturing environment for the children of st ud ents enrolled in the Yampah Teen Parent Program. It is also an edu cational re source for teen parents, and for other students at the school and in our community. We strive for excellence in meeting the needs of children and their families for nurturing growth, development, relationships, trust, happiness, safety, diversity, health and understanding. We have two fully equipped CO state licensed, 4-Star Qualistar rated nurseries, one for infants, newborn to age one, and one for toddlers age one to three and one half years old, with the capacity to serve 24 children each day.

name: THE GARDEN PRESCHOOL & EARLY LEARNING CENTER
details:
At the Garden Preschool, we strive to provide an environment that is emotionally secure and safe, where every child feels wanted and loved, and which promotes independence by offering choices and allowing the child to take the initiative. We believe in active learning, in encouraging children to manipulate materials, to use their senses to investigate, to explore by hands-on experience, and to search for answers to satisfy their curiosity. The classrooms are planned to include a wide variety of open ended activities and materials so that children can learn in their own way and at their own pace and level. We strive to highlight the unique strengths of every child, and to help each one become an independent thinker. 

Children learn best by first hand experience, and these experiences are the basis for new knowledge and growth. Family, community, and culture are by nature important to young children; their experiences in school allow them to make sense of their world and to further develop their perceptions. The Judaic aspects of The Garden Preschool curriculum (as all other aspects) are naturally and holistically woven into the child’s experience and are presented in a way that every child can be equally comfortable with.

Social relationships are crucial in so many areas of life, and a positive preschool experience is one of the most important keys to a child’s future success in connecting to other people. Teachers help children learn how to resolve conflicts without fighting, and they encourage the development of empathy and concern for others. 

The staff of The Garden Preschool & Early Learning Center looks forward to working together with you throughout the school year to help each child to succeed. We encourage you to ask questions about the program and to share your ideas with us.

name: GROWING YEARS SCHOOL
details:
The goal at GYS is to help young children make sense of the world. The intention is to provide a comfortable environment—one which is more home-like than school-like, creating an enthusiasm for learning, while developing good citizens. GYS exemplifies a high-quality, developmentally oriented program, delineating the best knowledge about how children grow and learn, providing for each child individually. In recognition that the arts are a basis of intellectual development, the program is rich in music, movement, visual and literary arts, and covers the rudiments of all disciplines from “astronomy to zoology.”
GYS is a school where a child can become self-confident and self-disciplined; where the child's individual talents and strengths are developed; where home and school cooperate; and where staff is open to learning, using observation and non-judgmental recording as a basis for program planning, implementation and assessment.

name: BOULDER VALLEY SCH DIST TEEN PARENT
details: The mission of the Boulder Valley School District is to create challenging, meaningful and engaging learning opportunities so that all children thrive and are prepared for successful, civically engaged lives.

name: CHILDREN'S CORNERSTONE LLC, AN EARLY LRNG CTR
VAIL CHILD CARE/EAGLE VALLEY CHILD CARE ASSOC
details:
The Eagle Valley Child Care Association aims to provide high quality early learning programs to the children of Eagle County by:

    Providing a developmentally appropriate, discovery based learning environment that meets the needs of every child’s healthy cognitive, language, motor, social and emotional development
    Providing supportive parenting guidance to every family enrolled in our programs
    Providing the business community with a way to assure quality care for their employees through our Business Partner program

name: LITTLE CHICKS & HATCHLINGS
details:
Little Chick’s specializes in children from 6 weeks to 3 years old. This inclusive environment allows us to provide for a child’s needs in 3 distinctive developmental age groups. Your 6 week to 15 month old starts in our “Pooh Room”. With a ratio of 1-5 we are able to focus developmental milestones using tummy time, sitting up, rolling over, songs, finger plays and other developmental activities.
In the “Very Hungary Caterpillar Room” our babies are transforming into pre-school kids. Children in this special classroom enjoy more fun and interactive self help activities such as painting, gluing, song, story time and other theme activities that are age appropriate for the kids in the class at that time.
Older children ready start being a big boy/girl will love the “Chicka Chicka Boom Boom” room as it is designed for self exploration while defining large motor skills. The pre-school activities start in this class with a more defined circle time, art activities, 3 step directions, potty training and all the extra fun things we offer based on the season and the age appropriateness in that class.
Once the children reach the age of 3 they are prepared to transfer to the Canyon Creek Academy which is just around the block. Here they will continue in their growth with pre-kindergarten prep and educational play.

name: OAK STREET CHILD DEVELOPMENT CENTER
details:
Oak Street Child Development Center, Inc. offers daycare and preschool services, as well as summer and after school care for children from 6 weeks to 12 years in Arvada, CO. We are more than just a babysitter, because we create a curriculum to meet every child’s individual needs, in order to prepare them for school and the social situations that may present themselves. Our low teacher/child ratio enhances our ability to provide the best environment for social and cognitive growth.

While we do have separate rooms for each age group, we decide if they are ready to go to the next room based on developmental skills and milestones, rather than birthdays.

Our Mission: Partnering with parents to provide a safe, dependable, educational and nurturing foundation for their children’s future.

name: POOH CORNER PRESCHOOL INC
details:
Vision Statement
We strive at Pooh Corner to provide a high quality environment to all children and families by developing a lifelong love for learning.

Mission Statement
Pooh Corner Preschool will create an inclusive environment
with children, families and the community by providing:
• A safe and nurturing environment.
• A balanced program that fosters self esteem.
• Enhancing social and emotional skills.
• Developmentally appropriate practices.
• Active hands - on learning.

name: EL NIDITO AT THE FAMILY CENTER
details:
Colorado Preschool Program (CPP) is a program that strives to serve the young children in Colorado who are most vulnerable to starting grade school unprepared. The legislature recognized that providing quality early childhood education would ultimately curb dropout rates, help children achieve their full potential, reduce dependence on public assistance, and decrease susceptibility to criminal activities.

    CPP provides free high quality preschool to eligible children through participating school districts and partnering community sites. There is no fee for children who qualify.
    Children are funded to attend preschool for a minimum of 10 hours per week during the school year. Preschool programs meet quality standards and limit class size to sixteen
    children with adult-to-child ratios of one-to-eight.

name: ROARING FORK SCHOOL DISTRICT - GSES
details: At GSES, we know that there is a relationship between our “habits” of work and learning and student achievement. Practicing our five habits help us to “do our best” and “be our best” in school and life every day.
business hours:
M,T,Th,F: 8:10-3:30 pm

Wednesdays: 8:10-2:00 pm (Enrichment Wednesdays dismisses at 3:30 pm)

Our office is open 30 minutes before and after school.

name: JULESBURG ELEMENTARY CHILD CARE CENTER
details:
Julesburg Elementary School is located in Julesburg, Colorado.  Julesburg is a small community consisting of 1300 people and sits in the far, northeast corner of the state.  It is the northernmost town in the state located less than one mile from the Nebraska border.

Julesburg Elementary is a public school servicing students preschool through 6th grades and averages approximately 144 students per year.  Julesburg Elementary School also maintains a Qualistar rated child care center which operates year-round.  Julesburg Elementary School maintains 13 full-time teachers and is holding steady at an approximate 17:1 student/teacher ratio.  The average years of experience for our educators is 21 years.

Julesburg Elementary School prides itself on the quality of education, the knowledge and experience of our staff, and the personal connections we have to our students.  We maintain traditional expectations while supporting and promoting the growth of a 21st Century learning environment.

name: BRIGHT BEGINNINGS, LLC
details:
At Bright Beginnings, we believe education begins at birth. Our program offers your child a variety of fun and challenging activities designed to stimulate their intellectual, physical and social development. Children engage in art, music, dramatic play, physical fitness and literature along with developing their cognitive skills, which include language and problem-solving abilities.

Our students enjoy spending time in the outdoor classroom, which includes aSensory Garden sensory garden to engage all of their budding senses. Our highly qualified, state-licensed teachers provide differentiated lessons in a supportive, caring environment.

As part of our comprehensive program, we serve well-balanced, state-approved meals and snacks at no additional charge. Lunch is served family style to promote conversation, independence appropriate manners and fine motor skills.

name: DAY ONE DAY CARE LEARNING CENTER
details: Day One Daycare Learning Center is a licensed childcare center that has been caring for children in a well-balanced, quality learning environment since 1990. Day One is licensed to serve 60 children ranging in age form 6 weeks to 10 years. The goal at Day One is to foster the social-emotional development of each child so that they learn self-confidence, respect for themselves and others, and the ability to resolve conflicts. The staff believes that building relationships with parents is important for each child to feel comfortable in their program. They provide interactions and experiences for children to build trust, to use their imaginations and creativity, and to learn the skills needed for success in life. Day One’s hours of operation are 6:30am to 6:00pm (allowing for 10-hour days), and it offers a free meals program that includes breakfast, lunch, and an evening snack.

name: KINGDOM LEARNING ACADEMY
details: Welcome to KINGDOM LEARNING ACADEMY!  It is a pleasure to serve you and your children and to be a part of their early learning.  Our Academy strives for excellence in preparing our children for Kindergarten and for enjoying successful lives!  The staff is well trained in early childhood education; as well, they are loving and devoted to meeting the needs of every child.  Our curriculum is diverse and is both creative and challenging, as our staff offers support and guidance to the children in our age-appropriate classrooms.  Our State license allows 58 children in our environment

name: WRAY COMMUNITY CHILD CARE CENTER
details: The Wray Community Learning Center is dedicated to quality care and education for your child. All of our friendly teachers are trained in early childhood education, so you can be assured that your child is getting the tools and knowledge they need. Our qualified staff goes the extra mile to intentionally engage children in hands-on learning on their level.

name: COLORADO EARLY LEARNING CENTER
details:
At Colorado Early Learning Center, we encourage children to learn through play and discovery in a safe and healthy environment.  Our staff is educated in early childhood development.  The curriculum at CELC will promote a stimulating yet structured environment in a developmentally appropriate way.  

Children will be encouraged to ask questions, explore their environment and develop a love for learning.  

Each child at CELC will be cherished for their individual differences and the staff will work to help promote their self-esteem, develop their self-confidence and guide them in learning diverse skills.  

We believe that the parent/guardian relationship is very important to a successful child care program.  CELC welcomes and encourages parents/guardians to visit and interact with their child during the hours the center is in operation.

name: ECEMS @ CSU - PUEBLO CHILD CARE CENTER
FIRST UNITED METHODIST CHRIST CHILDS SCHOOL
WESTWOOD CHILD DEVELOPMENT CENTER
details: MHM was incorporated in 1970 to provide affordable, accessible, quality early childhood care and education for children of low-income working parents. Over the past 40 years, the agency’s programs and scope of services have evolved to meet the changing needs of the community and incorporate the most recent knowledge in the field. Today, MHM is Denver’s oldest and largest provider of subsidized early childhood education and care, offering full-day, year-round programs in six centers serving Denver’s most distressed neighborhoods. In addition to the hundreds children served in these centers each year, MHM provides services for several additional thousand children in two drop-in centers for clients doing business with Denver Department of Human Services and the Denver court system.

name: CALHAN CHILDREN'S CENTER
details:
Calhan Children’s Center (CCC) is a Christian-based childcare facility and believe that each child is a unique individual and a gift from God. Calhan Children’s Center is an organization that values people: the children in our care, their parents, and our employees. Our staﬀ is highly experienced and educated, holding degrees in Early Childhood Education and Child Development, as well as certiﬁcation in First Aid, CPR, and Universal Precautions. We provide a physical environment that is safe, clean, healthy, and oriented to children. Each day, we serve nutritious home cooked meals with fresh fruits and veggies. CCC captures the essence of the home setting for children.

Our purpose is to provide children with the same type and quality of experience that they have at home and to enhance those experiences by capitalizing on the child’s receptivity to new learning and play. Our curriculum incorporates art, language & literacy, math, science, gross & ﬁne motor skills, music, religion, social & emotional, social studies, and sensory development into each age group at developmentally appropriate levels. From infants to school age, children enjoy a comprehensive experience in learning and play.

The summer program at CCC is remarkable. Children enjoy the luxury of going on several outings each week. These outings include events at Pikes Peak Library District, hikes to scenic locations both near and far, and swimming every Friday, to name a few. Time spent at the facility encompasses a variety of fun activities such as athletics, board games, art, and much more. The summer program is available for children in Kindergarten and up.

name: HARVARD ACADEMY
details: Early childhood learning for ages 8 weeks to five years. Before and after school/ Holiday care for ages 6 to 12 years.

name: CHRISTIAN COMMUNITY SCHOOL
details: Serving Christian families by providing a Christ-centered education that encourages academic excellence, spiritual development, and social responsibility, in an environment where students can develop their God-given gifts and talents, reaching the World for Jesus, one student at a time..."

name: CORNERSTONE MONTESSORI SCH
details: Cornerstone Montessori School's purpose is to provide quality Early Childhood Education (ECE) utilizing the Montessori method. Children in a Montessori environment learn through active discovery rather than through passive reception. All of our teachers have received specialized training in the Montessori method, which includes teachings, observations, and materials developed by Dr. Maria Montessori, as well as training in ECE. Our staff commits to each family enrolled in the school to support the discovery and development of the greatest potential within each child.
business hours: 7:00 a.m. to 6:00 p.m., Monday through Friday

name: HOSANNA EARLY LEARNING CENTER
details: Hosanna has been serving the southwest metro-Denver community for over 25 years, and we are still going strong! We have designed a unique and special program that allows children to grow and develop at their own rate in a loving, Christian environment. We take what each child has already acquired and help them build on that knowledge using a carefully made curriculum that focuses on the whole child and each of their needs. Because a child's work is play, we have a curriculum that allows children to play and they don't even realize that it is work! Plus, children get the knowledge that they are a special and unique person and how God's love is never ending!

name: CHILDRENS WORLD LEARNING CENTER
details: Children’s World Early Learning Center provides loving, Christ-centered care for children from six weeks through preschool. The mission of the center is to provide the highest quality child care in a safe, secure, yet stimulating environment where each child may experience success. Children are provided with nutritious meals, snacks, and opportunities to learn through age-appropriate activities. Our role is to extend, reinforce and complement a child’s home and family.

name: CHILDRENS GARDEN MONTESSORI SCHOOL DENVER
details: Children’s Garden Montessori School is a nurturing community of children, families and teachers, guided by the Montessori philosophy and influenced by the Reggio philosophy that educates young children and inspires a life-long love of learning.

name: ROCKY MOUNTAIN CHILDRENS DISCOVERY
details:
Rocky Mountain Children's Discovery Center offers Early Childhood Education to children ages 6 weeks through age 12. We are open year round, Monday-Friday, 6:30 am to 6:00 pm.
We believe children learn best in a setting that respects, values and encourages all aspects of the physical, emotional, social and cognitive development of each individual child. We believe that children benefit from an interactive and play based approach to learning. We strive to provide a climate that is inclusive in nature and reflective of the diversity of each child and family. We believe that families provide the foundation for learning. We believe that children need key experiences and adult support to grow and learn. We actively encourage a partnership with family members to enhance the potential of each child. We believe that the Rocky Mountain Children’s Discovery Center serves as a model in our community for collaboration and partnership development for the delivery of quality program services for children and families. We are proud of our status as a Qualistar rated preschool. We are proud to serve children who are enrolled in Early Childhood Special Education and in the Colorado Pre-school Program

name: NOAH'S ARK
details:
Noah’s Ark has served the Northern Metro Community for over 30 years. We are conveniently situated two blocks west of Federal on 104th Avenue– inside The Crossing Church.

Our center provides loving year round care for children 6 weeks through Pre-K as well as winter and summer break camps for older children. Our dedicated staff are eager to help your child grow into the person he or she can be!

name: OUR SCHOOL INC
details:
OUR School was founded in 1997, and we purchased our permanent facility in 2007.  OUR School is a private, licensed, non-profit, non-partisan, interracial, integrated program serving children aged 6 weeks to 6 years and their families.

A strong belief in children and families dominates the philosophy of OUR School.  OUR School is a developmentally oriented program which views its mission as providing the BEST early childhood educational program for children while they are away from their parents, while providing an equally important service to parents while they work.  OUR School is a supplement to, not a substitute for, each child’s family.  OUR goal is to provide a quality preschool experience for any child, including those with challenges, whether they be physical, emotional, or developmental.  We strive to provide quality care that is available, affordable, and accessible to all families living and working in the Roaring Fork Valley.

Ownership of OUR School is “ours”...children, parents and staff!

name: CONGREGATION RODEF SHALOM PRESCHOOL
details: Congregation Rodef Shalom, a participatory and egalitarian conservative synagogue, envisions itself as an extended Jewish Mishpucha (family) caring for all its members. Our sages teach us that Judaism is sustained by three things, by Torah (study), by Avodah (worship), and by Gimilut Chasedeem (acts of loving kindness). The Rodef Shalom family follows this teaching by serving the spiritual, educational, and social needs of its members and by so doing promotes the highest ideals of Conservative Judaism.
business hours: 7:00 am – 6:00 pm Monday – Thursday and 7:00 am – 4:00 pm on Fridays

name: LITTLE FRIENDS PRESCHOOL AND CHILD CTR
details:
Little Friends Learning Center provides quality full time preschool child care and instruction. The ratio of adults to children as set forth by the State of Colorado for child care for each age group will be maintained. The center is open from 7:00 AM until 6:00 PM Monday through Friday except on designated holidays.

Little Friends Learning Center serves breakfast, lunch and an afternoon snack daily which fulfill the standards set forth by the Child and Adult Care Food Program for nutritional needs of the various age levels served.

name: SUMMIT COUNTY PRESCHOOL
details:
The Summit School District Early Childhood Pr
ogram will provide enriching, developmentally
appropriate experiences for young children, em
power and support families as partners in
education, and collaborate with the community
in providing services to these children and
their families.

name: HOPE PARENT'S DAY OUT AND PRESCHOOL
details: The goal of Hope PDO & Preschool is to provide a program that benefits the child, parents, family, and community through a safe, interactive environment where children are provided with appropriate experiences and guidance that will encourage each child to reach his or her potential. All children are a gift from God, and each child is unique. Our approach to education is developmentally based and provides a safe, nurturing environment that promotes the emotional, social, intellectual, physical, and spiritual growth of children.

name: TAKE A BREAK
details:
The mission of Take-A-Break Incorporated is to provide the highest quality of child care available at an affordable rate while maintaining the highest standards achievable with well-trained, quality staff and excellent child/adult ratios. Our mission statement is congruent to the Take-A-Break philosophy which is:

One fleeting moment of joy will last a lifetime in the minds and hearts of our youth. Ours is the challenge to find the good in every child and to nurture it to its fullest potential – to encourage a positive outlook and attitude toward others and the future. The beauty, excitement, and sparkle brought forth from a child is worth all the world has to offer. Love, understanding, positive development and high self-esteem are the active ingredients of our pursuit.

name: WOODLAND PARK COMMUNITY CHURCH LEARNING CTR
details: The Woodland Park Community Church Learning Center is a licensed preschool facility that serves the families of Woodland Park and surrounding communities (Divide, Florissant, Lake George, Green Mountain Falls, Chipita Park, and Cascade) by providing early childhood education of the highest quality based in Christian practice and current research in child development and early childhood education. Loving, nurturing teachers provide daily learning opportunities in science, math, music, art literature, health and nutrition, social skills, and Christian nurture.

name: CHILDRENS CTR AT RED ROCKS COMM COLLEGE
details: Welcome to the Children's Center at Red Rocks Community College, a model training center and observation site for Early Childhood Education (ECE) students. Our center, conveniently located at the east entrance of the Lakewood campus, provides full-day quality care for children 18 months to kindergarten entry. Our clients are Red Rocks staff, students and members of the community.
business hours: Monday through Friday, 7:30 a.m. to 6:00 p.m.

name: SMART START LEARNING CENTER, LLC
details: Active Learners and Smart Start maintain a developmental philosophy of learning, which supports and respects the child as he/she is.  Our centers support the knowledge that children learn best through play and hands-on experiences.  Through the guidance of experienced teachers, the child will have the opportunity to explore and enrich his/her world socially, emotionally physically and intellectually toward optimal growth.

name: INTERNATIONAL LEARNING CENTER
details:
At International Learning Center, we welcome all families. Our focus is to develop children from diverse backgrounds, to appreciate enriching experiences, cultural diversity, and academic achievement, as we build each child’s learning skills. 

Our goal is to enrich the family by focusing on the whole child. We do this by providing a secure, safe, and home-style environment where the staff and parents work together in partnership while giving each child quality care, educational excellence, and developmental support. 

At International Learning Center, you will find caregivers who are educated, love children, and are always willing to care for each child as their own. Our providers are professionals who are proficient in the areas of early childhood development, cultural diversity, and a sincere desire to grow and develop children. 

We are proud to reflect our dedication to provide quality care, excellence in education, and open communication between parents and staff.

name: MCCOY & LITTLE JOHN CENTER
details: License by state regulation center in area of safety - class ratio - staff education and entrance requirements. Faith Base by committing to be greater care provider and have a vision for the children through showing them the fruits of the spirit Love, Joy, Peace, Patience, Kindness, Goodness, Faithfulness, Gentleness, and Self-Control. 32 Security Cameras Nutrition Meals Breakfast, AM Snack, Lunch, and PM Snack we provide children with healthy, nutrient rich meals posted for parents review. Communication through classroom management of appropriate discipline, positive communication and age appropriate education and life skills to maintain a clean safe environment.

name: CREATIVE KIDS CORNER
details: At Creative Kids Corner, CKC, we work with you and your child in every way we can to facilitate your child’s adjustment. We want the time your child spends in our care to be a rewarding, happy, and fulfilling experience. We are locally owned and operated and strive to provide you with the highest quality care possible. You may contact us by telephone, email, or simply drop by CKC and see our facilities in person. We are located in Wellington, Colorado, a short ten minute drive from Fort Collins traveling 1-25.

name: VENTURE FOR SUCCESS CHILDCARE LEARNING
details:
This program is designed to ready your child for the 1st grade.  Here your child will experience proven techniques that helps the management of emotions and the ability to establish positive and rewarding relationships with others. 

​Our program encompasses both intra- and interpersonal processes.  The core features of emotional development include the ability to identify and understand one’s own feelings, to accurately read and comprehend emotional states in others, to manage strong emotions and their expression in a constructive manner, to regulate one’s own behavior, to develop empathy for others, and to establish and maintain relationships.

name: STEP BY STEP TEEN PARENT PROGRAM
NEW CREATION PRESCHOOL
details: Our school is open to all children in our community between the ages of 2 and 5 years old. We offer a faith based, developmentally appropriate preschool with extended hour for working parents. The preschool is a non-profit organization that is under the governing board of New Creation Church. New Creation Preschool is located at 226 Center Drive in Glenwood Springs. We are open year round except for major holidays.

name: COLONNADE CHILDREN'S CENTER
details: Colonnade is a small child care center located within the Cesar Chavez Building. We are licensed for 53 children, from infants through preschool. We have two playgrounds, a new facility completed in 2012, and a marvelous staff of 16. We serve Federal parents along the general public.   We are dedicated to implementing best practices in the care and education of young children. We foster children’s individual development and support the unique needs of families, staff and community.

name: CHILDREN'S CORNER LEARNING CENTER
details:
At the Children’s Corner Learning Center, our first and strongest belief is that all children have the right to a safe, warm, clean and nurturing environment. It is our job and pleasure to provide such an environment for all children involved in our program. We also operate on the belief that all children are capable and have potential, that they construct their own learning, and that they bring with them a natural need and desire to explore. This desire must be actively encouraged, nurtured, and guided. We believe that children’s learning is optimized when they are actively engaged in child-directed activities that peak their curiosity and imagination and when these activities have personal meaning to them.

Furthermore, we believe that the children are part of a larger picture of family and the outside community. Parents are strongly encouraged and supported in being an active part of the center and their child’s learning. Children are involved with the outside community through activities both at the center and outside the center.

The Children’s Corner Learning Center is committed to providing children with a safe and pleasant school environment while being stimulated in the areas of social, ethical, physical, artistic and intellectual development.

name: KIDDIELAND EARLY CHILD CARE & EDUCATION CTR
FIRST UNITED METHODIST WEE CARE CENTER
NORTH ROUTT PRESCHOOL & EARLY LEARNING CENTER
details:
At North Routt Preschool we encourage children to be active members of the learning process.  We acknowledge that young children learn from their
experiences and from their relationships.  We strive to support them in this process by offering many and varied experiences and by honoring their relationships with family, friends and community. 

The curriculum at North Routt Preschool uses a project-based approach to learning that honors the Reggio Emilia philosphy.  Students participate in small group or large group projects developed out of their interests and expanded by their own ideas.  Projects can span over a number of days or months.  Some recent projects include a community garden project, worm composting, and creating an outdoor marble run. 

Through a strong partnership with nearby North Routt Community Charter School and with the Clark, CO community, North Routt Preschool encourages its students to care for each other and for their community.  Collaborative programs such as library story time with the kindergarteners and PE with the fifth and sixth graders help to expand and enrich the relationships of our young students.

name: SILVERTON FAMILY LEARNING CENTER
details:
The Silverton Family Learning Center’s mission is to guide students to reach their creative, intellectual, social and physical potential. We value the imagination and curiosity of children and respect childhood as an integral part of life. Our teachers challenge students to question, to think, to collaborate and to act with integrity. Our school works in partnership with families to teach personal and social responsibility, and to create a community that honors diversity and our common humanity. SFLC inspires students and community members to be lifelong learners with the courage and confidence to make a positive contribution to the world.

SFLC is open to part-time and year-round Silverton residents as well as for drop-in care for families visiting Silverton any time of the year.  Please contact us should you be interested in bringing your little one to SFLC.
- See more at: http://sflc.co/#sthash.rUjGJ7Ba.dpuf

Each child and family is important! We help foster a sense of creativity and positive self-esteem through hands-on, discovery-based activities. Children’s Garden Learning Center is more than a day care!

At Children's Playland our mission is to provide the best-possible care and creative, play-based education for young children with a caring, safe and supportive environment. Through this we foster social, creative, emotional, physical and intellectual development for the children in our care.
Vision Statement:
Our vision is that Children's Playland will set the standard for quality child care services through our innovative approach to the changing needs of the families we serve. We will encourage the children in our care to grow up to be healthy, productive members of society through a creative, play-based learning experience. We will strive to create a developmentally appropriate environment that will provide a stimulating educational experience and foster a desire to become a life-long learner in each child.

details: MHM was incorporated in 1970 to provide affordable, accessible, quality early childhood care and education for children of low-income working parents. Over the past 40 years, the agency’s programs and scope of services have evolved to meet the changing needs of the community and incorporate the most recent knowledge in the field. Today, MHM is Denver’s oldest and largest provider of subsidized early childhood education and care, offering full-day, year-round programs in six centers serving Denver’s most distressed neighborhoods. In addition to the hundreds children served in these centers each year, MHM provides services for several additional thousand children in two drop-in centers for clients doing business with Denver Department of Human Services and the Denver court system.

Mission Hills Early Learning Center provides weekly, theme based units. These units provide the children with guidance in their daily activities. The units help develop social skills, language skills, prewriting skills, and prereading skills. The units are appropriate for each child’s individual developmental stage.

The preschool provides the children with hands-on experiences. We offer low child/staff ratios in all of our classrooms.

Our staff are loving, caring individuals who have a personal love of the Lord.  We aspire to make a difference in the lives of children, families, and the community.

name: TEMPLE EMANUEL EARLY CHILDHOOD CENTER

Temple Emanuel Early Childhood Center follows the Jewish calendar with a well-rounded, age appropriate Jewish curriculum. Jewish vales are taught to instill an ethical model for living.
Teachers

We take pride in our quality teaching staff. The teacher/child ratios exceed state requirements to maintain the highest standards of education for our children. Dedicated teachers provide a climate that enables each child to develop socially, intellectually and emotionally. Our primary objective is to make each child feel attending school is a natural, exciting experience.
Curriculum

Developmentally-appropriate skills and concepts, and group interactions such as how to take turns and make new friends, are introduced in a safe, loving and nurturing environment. We have an emergent curriculum which cultivates the child’s interest and builds their developmental skills.

Temple Emanuel Early Childhood Center is a warm, nurturing and safe environment where each child is appreciated for his/her unique qualities. Our school is a diverse community where everyone respects one another.

name: ST. THOMAS MORE PARENT'S DAY OUT & PRESCHOOL
details:
STM Catholic is a parochial school, deeply rooted in the Gospel of Jesus Christ and the teaching of the Catholic Church. In the great tradition of Catholic education, we remain devoted to the development of the whole person in each of our students.

The School strives to nurture in its students, an awareness and love of God and a sense of moral responsibility. We believe that the spiritual growth of our students gives meaning to their intellectual and physical pursuits. We hold that it is only in the context of valuing their relationship with God, discovering their individual gifts and talents, and accepting their responsibilities toward self and community, that they can pursue an education that prepares them to lead fulfilling lives.

STM Catholic encourages each of its students to actively seek knowledge and understanding in pursuit of the truth. The objective of the School's rigorous academic program is to develop in each student the skills of examination and expression; to provide a solid foundation in the fundamental fields of human knowledge; to cultivate an ability to think critically, creatively, and independently; and to inspire intellectual curiosity and a passion for learning.

Also integral to the STM Catholic experience, our physical education and athletic programs serve to instill certain qualities of character; to develop strength of body and alertness of mind; and to illuminate the value of life-long fitness and health. Emphasizing self-discipline, teamwork, perseverance, sportsmanship, and striving toward a goal, the physical dimension of an STM Catholic education provides important lessons for life's challenges.
- See more at: http://www.stmcatholic.org/about-us/mission-philosophy#sthash.d1nlO9hr.dpuf

name: IMAGINATION + CHILD DEV CENTER - PARKER
details: Welcome to Imagination Plus Child Care Centers in Parker, Colorado. We are so excited at the opportunity to provide loving and nurturing preschool, infant and toddler care, and private kindergarten programs for your child. Our preschool provides a rich and diverse curriculum that is enhanced through play, cooking, and weekly themes. The center offers preschool, infant care, toddler care, private kindergarten, before/after school and track break program for older students as well. Our center is conveniently located for families in Parker, Castle Rock, Castle Pines, and Franktown.

name: RISING STAR EARLY LEARNING CENTER

details:
Welcome to the wonderful world of learning at Basalt Elementary School! This is a very special and important time in your child's life. Early learning is critical to a child's continued success in school and our philosophy in all of our classrooms is to focus on each child's needs to create an environment where all students show success in their learning.

Our school offers the choice of Dual Language Bilingual program at all grade levels. Our school also offers many programs to meet student needs including a Gifted and Talented (PEAK) Program, Environmental Education, Outdoor Education Field Trips, Grade Level Plays, Counseling Services, English Language instruction as well as many others.

Basalt Elementary School is closed to any new enrollment outside of the Basalt attendance area (Old Snowmass to Blue Lake Subdivision). This decision was made due to the fact that enrollment at BES has reached maximum optimal capacity.

name: BRUSH CREEK ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details:
Brush Creek Elementary is a Colorado John Irwin School of Excellence serving the community of Eagle Ranch in Eagle. John Irwin schools demonstrate excellent academic achievement that exceeds expectations established by the Colorado Department of Education.

To provide the highest quality academic experience for our students so they succeed in the 21st Century.

Vision
A safe, collaborative and rigorous learning environment in which all students are held to high expectations and are active participants in their learning process.

Cherry Creek Presbyterian Church offers two weekday programs for young children. The mission of our Christian school programs is to promote the growth and development of the young child in a Christ-centered environment.

The curriculum is designed to offer age-appropriate educational activities, reinforce the excitement of learning and establish personal and social skills. The programs offer a safe, nurturing and stimulating environment in which children will develop self-esteem and respect for others as well as grow in their love of God and His creation.

name: VICTORY MONTESSORI AND CHILDCARE

Our childcare program is a year round program and our Montessori school is on a school year schedule. Our center is licensed by the Colorado Department of Social Services. We have been in operation since 1990.

Our vision is to provide a safe Christian environment that will meet the needs of your children and challenge them spiritually, physically, mentally, and emotionally. We do this through a structured curriculum. Each classroom has a strong early childhood basis and is developmentally appropriate for the age levels we serve. Lesson plans are implemented in classrooms from age two through Pre-Kindergarten. We teach Christian values by daily devotions, music, Bible stories and modeling. Our desire is to see children achieve on the levels that the Lord has designed for them.

name: CHERRY HILLS CHRISTIAN PRESCHOOL
details:
Cherry Hills Christian is committed to educating the whole child. Our students' foundation is God's truth found in His Word, the Bible. We strive to provide excellent academics. We are equally concerned with spiritual, emotional and social development of our students. We believe God created each child as His divine masterpiece, capable as learners and uniquely gifted for His purpose. Truth and knowledge are taught through a distinctly Biblical perspective and worldview. A variety of developmentally appropriate instructional strategies and methodologies are intentionally utilized to honor children's individual differences, actively engaging them in their learning.

Since children learn best in a physically, emotionally and spiritually safe and nurturing atmosphere, teachers are committed to supporting the development of positive relationships. Cherry Hills Christian is privileged to come along side each child as they grow in their faith, develop Christ-like character, learn discernment and utilize their God-given gifts and talents to honor Him.

We are licensed, locally owned and operated. Our teachers are qualified for all ages and references are available. Our before and after school care fees also include bus transportation. We care for children aged one year to 12 years. For the best in child care and early learning, come to the professionals at Wooden Shoe Pre-School & Pre-Kindergarten!

details: The Little Mavericks Learning Center provides a service to Colorado Mesa University students, faculty and staff, by providing quality child care with a balanced curriculum geared to the age and developmental level of the children while providing a practicum lab opportunity for students at Colorado Mesa University. Little Mavs provides experiences that enrich each child's cognitive, social, emotional, physical and creative development through play-based activities. Each child has the opportunity to create and explore their environment and learn problem solving skills while developing personal interaction skills. details: Zach's place was established to provide families in the Colorado Springs and surrounding areas a place for respite care for their children with disabilities ages 2 to 21. We provide respite (temporary time apart for parent/caregiver and child) in a home-like environment and also have children daily after school and on school breaks. We aim to provide very flexible scheduling and individualized support so as to serve as many families as we can, with most families currently using our services after school and any time on weekends. name: LAKE GEORGE ELEMENTARY PRESCHOOL
details: A charter school in Colorado is a school that is funded through district revenues but governed by a separate board.  LGCS became a charter school in 1996, to allow our community greater autonomy in governance, finances and general operations.  We are still a public school, but our employees are charter school employees, and our budget, policies and procedure are determined by our Charter School Board.  We are unique in the state of Colorado, in that we were one of the first charter schools to be formed from previous district schools, operating in district buildings.  Because of our unique status, we are considered "pioneers" among rural Colorado communities who wish to establish greater local autonomy for their schools. Today, Cottonwood Preschool is one of a handful of parent cooperative preschools in the Denver area. We continue to have a very dedicated group of parents who are committed to carrying on the tradition of excellence at Cottonwood.

Cottonwood embraces a developmental philosophy of learning, which supports and respects the child as he/she is. The teachers at Dream Makers are experienced, compassionate, and engaging with the children. Deb was formerly a kindergarten teacher and knows just how to prepare children for this transition.

The emphasis at Dream Makers is learning through FUN. Dream Makers teachers notice what each child is interested in and builds upon that. Children are treated as individuals. Dream Makers does some non-traditional things too, like welcoming the occasional animal visitor. Some visitors we’ve had are dogs, pigs, and goats!

Dream Makers has several parent’s nights where we get to engage with each other and do a craft like building gingerbread houses, make and enjoy stone soup, and more. Read what parents and inspectors have said about us or just schedule a time to visit so you can see what makes us so special!

Jefferson Street Preschool is dedicated to providing a loving, nurturing, and enriching environment in which children explore, learn and grow.  Our program is open to children 2 1/2 - 5 years of age.  Children are supported in exploring their curiosity and knowledge of the world while working on social skills, and becoming prepared for later learning years.  Our program recognizes that children learn in their own unique way.  Through child initiated, teacher enhanced interactions your child will have many opportunities to build self-confidence, positive peer connections, and a love for learning.

Bree Schaffer is the Director of Jefferson Street Preschool and a Colorado native, growing up in Littleton. She moved to Boulder for college, attending    CU and graduating with a B.A. in Psychology and Spanish in 2008.  Bree spent the entirety of her college years volunteering for and later directing a support and crisis line, and she wholeheartedly believed that she wanted to be a therapist.  It wasn’t until she worked at a summer camp after graduating that  Bree found her true passion in working with young children.  After the camp ended, she started teaching in the Early Childhood field.  She took additional college classes to become both an Early Childhood Teacher and Small Center Director Qualified. In the process of doing that, Bree also became a Child Health Liaison through Boulder County Public Health. Her education in early childhood is ongoing and she really enjoys learning about how she can best support children and their families. She has been at Jefferson Street Preschool since it opened and loves her JSP community.

Eli Fairman, although born in Germany, grew up mainly in Colorado. He became used to being the “new kid” in school due to his father’s Air Force career and thus can understand the anxiety some of our children will encounter on their first day of school. Eli loves competing in sports, especially football, wrestling and lacrosse. He is looking forward to completing his education and starting a family. Although young, Eli’s character is evident by his respect for others, empathy for those less fortunate and his recognition of virtue in everyone. We see him as a strong, positive and encouraging role model for the students at Jefferson Street Preschool and feeling very fortunate to have him on our team.

Sewall’s mission is to assist all children (birth to age 6) and their families to achieve their highest potential. Its dedicated team of professionals is committed to meeting the needs of and enhancing opportunities for young children, including those with special needs due to disabilities, developmental delays, and economic disadvantages.
 
In Sewall’s inclusive preschool program, children with disabilities and delays learn side by side with their peers who are typically developing. Through this immersion with others whose abilities and experiences differ, children naturally build empathy for others, leading to a lifetime of understanding and acceptance.Multi-age classrooms are staffed by early childhood educators and supported by early childhood special educators, occupational and physical therapists, speech pathologists and mental health professionals, and therapeutic interventions are provided within the natural setting of the classroom. This transdisciplinary model means Sewall’s preschool classrooms have ratios of one adult for every five children. The preschool program serves children at Sewall and at satellite sites, making high-quality early intervention more geographically accessible for families with children with special needs.

Sewall offers a nationally-recognized, four-star Qualistar-rated. It utilizes only developmentally appropriate practices and maintains rigorous standards so that it consistently provides the highest quality programs and services.

Mission
Granby Play Days Preschool uses play and creative interaction as a way for children to discover and learn. Our ultimate goal is to prepare our students to be kindergartners who enjoy learning and who are ready to learn. To reach that goal we have three objectives:
• To provide an environment which enhances social competency, language skills, emotional and physical growth and well-being, dramatic play and creative self expression.
• To provide a nurturing environment which models positive interaction with the world and others.
• To provide an enjoyable group experience that respects individual learning styles and facilitates lifelong learners.

Granby Play Days Preschool was formed in May of 2009 when it was learned that two preschools in central Grand County were closing (the C Lazy U Preschool and the Mountain Family Center Preschool in Grand Lake). Some staff and parents of C Lazy U Preschool were urged to begin efforts to offer a new preschool in the Granby area that would fill the void left by the closure of the two schools.

Granby Play Days offers a Kindergarten-prep program that is geared toward preparing young children (ages 2.5 to 5) for elementary school. We believe this can best be done by “discovering and learning through play.”

We believe that a solid preschool education prepares children so they can arrive at Kindergarten ready and prepared to learn, both intellectually and socially. Our curriculum also teaches a range of social and development skills that nurture that best practices for preparing children to learn in a group/community setting. These skills are lifetime skills that translate into long term social gains.

Summer Camps for preschool age children are held during June and July.

name: CHIPETA PRESCHOOL
details: Chipeta was born June 10, 1843 somewhere in the Conejos Colorado area. She was a Taviwach Nuche and the wife of Chief Ouray. They made their home south of the Present day Montrose along the Uncompahgre River. Chipeta was known for her compassion for peace and her steady strength in supporting her husband's goal to keep his people, the Utes in Colorado and out of harm’s way. She accompanied Ouray to Washington where she was treated as royalty and was referred to as the "Mountain Princess." She accepted all of this attention in a graceful way. People came to her for christening of their children and to ask her to cure the sick. She raised two children as if she gave birth to them, they were Cooroopoits and James McCook, Cooroopoits was the daughter of Ouray's brother and the sister of Chipeta. it is the custom of our people to give when someone cannot have. Chipeta did not have any children of her own. She was known for her beading, and for making clothing out of buckskin and giving gifts that she had made. She lost Ouray in 1880 due to Bright Disease.  She was forced to move to Utah along with her people. She lived to be 81 years old living in Bitter Creek where she died on August 17, 1921. Because her grave was deteriorating so badly, her brother John, with the aid of the Indian agent in Utah arranged for her reburial on the same location of her former ranch south of Montrose, Colorado. In 1925 she was reinterred at her former ranch south of Montrose. 5,000 people attended this event. Her brother John and a family friend Yagah, were the only family members who were able to make the trip.

details:
Woodlin School District R-104 is a single-campus district, housing grades Pre-K to 12, located on the Eastern Plains of Colorado in southwestern Washington County. Three small communities surround Woodlin: Last Chance, Lindon, and Woodrow. The main tax base is agriculture. All of the students are bused to school except for the teachers’ children who live on campus housing, and some High School students who drive themselves.

The Woodlin school system has a student teacher ratio of approximately eight to one. School is in session from 8:00 am to 4:00 pm Tuesday through Friday. Occasionally a Monday is scheduled to provide the required student contact days.

The school facility consists of two buildings. The main building houses the office, library, cafeteria, elementary and secondary classrooms. A secondary math classroom, fine arts department and excellent auditorium are located in the adjacent building.

The school is the center of many activities for our area. The local Lions Club meets at the school in the evenings. The Lions Club supports the school by providing scholarships and other helpful work around the school. The school is used for a variety of community events.

The school district has a distance learning program in cooperation with other school districts throughout the East Central Board of Cooperative Educational Services. This system allows the district to expand course offerings and programs for our students. A feature of our program made possible by this system is the “Sophomore Scholars” program, in which students can earn an Associate’s Degree from Morgan Community College by taking courses for dual high school /college credit in their junior and senior years. After graduation, the student can then attend any Morgan Community College campus to complete their associate degree.

Preschool programs are available at most neighborhood elementary schools and designated community sites.

name: ROARING FORK SCH DIST PRESCHOOL PROG
details: CRES Preschool consists of two inclusive classrooms, in the Early Childhood wing of Crystal River Elementary School. We value diversity in our classrooms and offer high-quality early childhood experiences to children who come to us with different languages, backgrounds, and abilities. There are two qualified teachers in each classroom of up to 16 children, and there may also be an extra special education paraprofessional to work with a child one-on-one if there is a child who needs extra support. CRES preschools use Project Approach curriculum, which follows the interests of the children and guides them through play-based research and investigations that build on their natural dispositions to be intellectually curious and to investigate their environments. Projects usually last a month or more to give young children the opportunity to fully immerse themselves in the project and/or investigation for greater understanding of each topic.

name: KENDRICK LAKES PRESCHOOL
details:
Our preschool accepts and respects the whole child at his/her developmental stage and cultural background. We provide children opportunities and experiences to grow both academically and socially.

name: LEAWOOD PRESCHOOL

name: HOFF ELEMENTARY PRESCHOOL
details:
Our goal is that children will be provided multiple opportunities for success as they grow intellectually, socially, and emotionally during their elementary years. Now that a new year of formal learning has begun, students are striving to align their learning and social habits to the HOWL. By doing so, they will continue to grow and develop into productive citizens at home, at school, in the community, and beyond.
At Hoff, we truly believe all children can learn. Our on-going vision for Hoff Elementary is to maximize individual student achievement in a safe school environment where students and staff are part of a learning community.  Teachers and students alike are encouraged to take risks with new learning. Your contribution as a parent includes helping your child be at school every day and supporting their learning endeavors from home. Whether you volunteer at school and/or support your child’s learning at home by providing them with a supportive study environment, your involvement is important and welcomed.  Please feel free to visit at Hoff Elementary.

details:
Opened in 1999, Eagle Crest is located in the southwest part of Longmont. Named for the eagles that used to nest in the area, the school's colors and mascot were chosen by the 5th graders attending school here in 1999. Original student artwork was designed and submitted for the golden eagle mascot.

Eagle Crest Elementary is currently a Pre-K through 5th grade elementary school. Kindergarten includes half day classes and full day tuition based classes. Please contact our office for the most current information regarding kindergarten

A preschool program, one for three year olds and one for four year olds, is also offered

Eagle Crest is also unique in that we are a looping school. Looping involves teachers keeping the same students for two years in grades 1 and 2 and grades 3 and 4.

name: NEW HORIZONS COOPERATIVE PRESCHOOL
details: We value diversity in culture, class, language, ethnicity, ability, and individual expression, and we believe that people thrive in an environment where each person is honored and respected for their differences and commonalities. Our goal is to develop in each child an appreciation of his or her unique voice, as well as a sense of wonder and respect for the beautiful and diverse world in which we live.  As our children take their place in our increasingly complex, global world, they will have some deep resources to draw upon, having learned in preschool the importance of respect, kindness and friendship in solving problems of all kinds.

name: EMMANUEL UMC PRESCHOOL
details:
Emmanuel Methodist is a community, non-denominational preschool that is committed to providing an age-appropriate educational curriculum designed to stimulate curiosity, reinforce the excitement of learning, and establish personal and social skills necessary for future success in school.  The school has been in operation for 42 years and has served over 1,800 families.

The program offers a safe, nurturing and stimulating atmosphere in which children will develop self-esteem, respect for others and growth in independence.  Children at our school are encouraged to learn through play experiences.

Emmanuel Methodist Preschool is a member of the Denver Preschool Program with a four star rating from Qualistar.  This membership entitles Denver parents, with a four year old, whose fourth birthday falls before October 1, to apply for tuition credits for a discount in their monthly tuition.  With these credentials, EMP gains access to free materials and supplies as well as continuing professional development courses for our teachers.
business hours: 9:00 a.m. – 1:00 p.m.Monday through Thursday and from 9:00 a.m. - 12:00 p.m on Friday

name: MOUNTAIN VALLEY LUTHERAN PRESCHOOL
details:
Mountain Valley Lutheran Church praises and glorifies God by sharing the gospel with our community and by nurturing one another through word and sacrament. As a ministry of MVLC, MVLP furthers the church’s mission statement by teaching the children and their families the truth of God’s Word.

Mountain Valley Lutheran Preschool provides children with a high quality Christian education as it encourages, supports and nurtures its families through the Word of God. Christian preschool education fosters the faith of each child and supports Christian parenthood and home life. It provides kindergarten readiness and develops students’ academic, social and emotional abilities; understanding that each child learns at different rates, depending on their own God-given capabilities and desires.
​
Jane Merten serves as director and teacher. She holds a bachelor’s degree in education and is certified by the State of Colorado as an early childhood large center director. Janine Kirk serves as teacher. She has many years of early childhood education experience. Janine has her large center certificate.
​
Children must be 3 years old and potty-trained to be eligible. Our license allows us to have up to 20 children at a time, but we limit enrollment to 15 per day in order to achieve a lower child-to-teacher ratio.  Earliest drop-off is 7:45am. The school day begins at 8:15am. Latest pick-up is 3:15pm. We generally follow the Eagle County School District calendar, so that we are not in session during the summer months or on typical holidays and school vacations. VIEW CALENDAR.

name: JEFFERSON COUNTY OPEN SCHOOL PRESCHOOL
details: Our school is a pre-kindergarten through 12th grade community, where students of all ages interact and learn from each other. Self-direction is a fundamental principle of our school. Our students are engaged in and in charge of their own learning. The world is our classroom! Elementary students begin with overnight camping trips and secondary students travel the world. The Open School provides a dynamic environment that fosters the development of the unique potential in each individual by nurturing and challenging the whole person. There is an emphasis on self-direction, learning through experience, shared responsibility, and the development of life long-skills.

Our management staff includes the RD-2 Superintendent as our Executive Director, a Head Start Director, Family Services Coordinator and Education Coordinator.  We employ a teacher, assistant teacher, and classroom aide in each center.  Our food and transportation services are provided through the respective school districts.

details:
Telluride Preschool was founded in 1994 and in that time, has seen hundreds of children pass through its doors. We pride ourselves on creating a comfortable, nurturing setting that fosters self-esteem and establishes trust. We aim to understand and encourage individual talents and interests to create a positive atmosphere with regard to learning.

Our school offers a variety of materials and activities so kids can playfully explore and become better aware of their surroundings. We also engage in enrichment programs outside our facility that we believe enhance the overall preschool experience. Above all, we want our kids to have fun while learning and to have a smooth transition into elementary school.

Some of the developmental skills we work on include: fine motor, gross motor, language, art, beginning math, science, phonics/early reading, listening, and social studies.

name: SHRINE OF ST THERESE CATHOLIC PRSCHL
details:
St. Therese Catholic School’s mission is to prepare our students for the academic demands and spiritual challenges of a 21st Century community.   We ensure academic achievement through a traditional pre-collegiate curriculum integrated within the teachings of Catholic tradition, and built upon the underlying principles of rigor and reason.  St. Therese Catholic School has not adopted "The Common Core" and does not report any student information to any agencies outside of the Diocese of Pueblo.

In addition to a full academic program of Language Arts, Mathematics, Science, and Social Studies, we provide an active enrichment program consisting of Spanish, Vocal Music, Physical Education, and Religious Studies daily.   Student learning is supported by a wide range of field trip experiences, grade level projects, and integrated instructional technology. 

St. Therese provides a comprehensive Middle School program taught by fully certified/highly qualified secondary teachers focused on pre-collegiate preparation.  St. Therese also provides a High School experience on campus for students in grades 9 thru 12.  The program includes online course work through Catholic Schools of Excellence, a nationally accredited  online instructional program.  In additon, juniors and seniors have the opportunity to take advantage of the "Concurrent Enrollment Program" offered at near by Pueblo Community College or at Colorado State University - Pueblo. The school is led by an experienced principal with over thirty years in education and a Board of Directors appointed by the Bishop.

Rascals toddler program (ages 1-3) offers a warm, loving environment with a focus on making friends, sharing, listening, following directions, communicating with words and more. Located at 405 Society Dr. 

Rainbow preschool program (3-5-year-olds) focuses on teaching children important social skills as well as preparing them for Kindergarten. Rainbow strives to make school fun and interesting so children are excited to learn the rest of their lives. Located at 538 W. Colorado Ave.

Rockies afterschool/summer camp program (5-7 years old). The program offers an abundance of activities and field trips, while focusing on creative outlets for expression and social interaction with peers. Located at 538 W. Colorado Ave.

details:
The North Fork Community Montessori School’s mission is to nurture each child’s natural desire to learn and passion for discovery. The school stresses innovative problem solving and encourages life-long learning.

In a creatively-structured environment, inclusive of all cultures, we will promote excellence in academics, art and life skills, while respecting individual uniqueness. We strive to inspire responsibility and respect for self, community and environment.

name: ACTIVE LEARNING CENTER
details: Active Learning Center (ALC) is a small, privately-operated early learning center that is accredited through NAEYC (National Association for the Education of Young Children) located in Denver, CO. Both full and part-time enrollment is available for children ages 3-5. ALC uses a Reggio-Emilia inspired curriculum that focuses on the whole child and includes language, social, emotional, cognitive and physical development. The program is designed to guide children’s learning in an active and engaging way all within a rich educational environment. Active Learning Center’s staff has educational backgrounds as well as years of experience in the field of early childhood education. All teachers are trained in the Reggio Approach and our low turnover allows children to develop strong relationships with their caregivers.

name: PRE KAMP VAIL I
details: Pre Kamp Vail recognizes the recreational desires of young children and how to provide adventure for children with little legs and big spirits. The low camper-to-counselor ratio allows your camper to receive individual attention as they enjoy self-directed play, arts and crafts, songs, games and a daily adventure outing.

name: SECURITY DAY CARE CENTER
details: We are excited to be here providing high quality pre-school/child-care and school-age programs for children since 1967. Security Daycare Center, known as, The Security School is medium in size and large in care and service to children and families. We are uniquely situated in a comfortable setting with four separate and distinct classrooms. Our playground is relatively large and accommodated with a full array of shade trees and play equipment, including good old sand and dirt boxes to properly excavate a new imaginary world each day.

All food provided to our students is organic. 

Throughout the year we partner with the many resources of the Summit County Community such as the Breckenridge Nature Series, the National Repertory Orchestra, Vail Resorts, and the Breckenridge Recreation Center to further enrich our curriculm. Since our opening in 2006, Breckenridge Montessori has veen proud to receive an Excellence in Childcare Award from Summit County, a Full Membership Level Award from the American Montessori Society, a Three Star (out of 4) Qualistar Rating Award from Qualistar Early Learning, an Eco-Healthy Childcare Designation by the Oregon Environmental Council, and successful completion of the Program Administration Scale for Early Childhood Leadership and Management.
